content.title: Timex Men's Easy Reader Watch
content.top_review:
I’m very pleased with this watch.  I’ve had it three weeks and it has been keeping good time.  I like the gold/brass color of the case and the clarity of the glass.  The face is easy to read and the cream face color is handsome and a nice contrast, less glaring than the white my previous Timex had.  Setting the date is not a problem, as some other reviews have stated.  Once you find the required “middle” position of the stem between all the way in and all the way out, it becomes pretty natural and is easy to remember.  Speaking of the date, I wish they kept the day of the week presentation that my previous Timex had, but that’s a relatively small disappointment.  The band is excellent.  It’s a soft suede-like leather that’s very flexible.  The trim stitching is very well done; straight, even,  and all finishings are secured and tucked away so that there are no loose ends or fraying looks.  The two belt loops, one fixed close behind the buckle and the other sliding further down the strap are great for keeping the strap close to the wrist.  All-in-all, a great buy for the price!
  
Read more
